<span id="freeTextContainer7838943146721345947">Yes, you are stuck: Juliette Binoche is Vianne Rocher, and you can&apos;t work your way around it, unless you&apos;ve spent the past two decades under a rock. But, let&apos;s face it, she was at least appropriately cast, and you&apos;ll get through it.<br/><br/>Beyond that, it turns out this novel is like a refreshing and delicious wind that blows in your direction right when you need it. <br/><br/>And, naturally, by the end of the novel, you&apos;re ransacking your kitchen for chocolate.</span>
  <span id="freeText7838943146721345947" style="display:none">Yes, you are stuck: Juliette Binoche is Vianne Rocher, and you can't work your way around it, unless you've spent the past two decades under a rock. But, let's face it, she was at least appropriately cast, and you'll get through it.<br /><br />Beyond that, it turns out this novel is like a refreshing and delicious wind that blows in your direction right when you need it. <br /><br />And, naturally, by the end of the novel, you're ransacking your kitchen for chocolate.</span>
